          h2.mb-20
            |  Caulking 
          p
            |  At Titan Group, we will inspect the property and locate entire cable trays that pass through a wall opening. We will then fill the opening with fire-stopping material. Many fire-stopping products employ intumescent materials that, when exposed to heat, expand to fill any voids in the penetration. Typically these products include fire-stop mortar, caulk, putty sticks, blocks, and pillows. Fire-stop mortar and caulk are semipermanent products. At Titan, we will apply the caulk to the penetration with a hand-held caulk gun. We will also use the mortar with a trowel. If the opening is small enough, we will apply putty sticks and mold it around the cables, conduit, and pipes that penetrate the fire-resistive barrier. Depending on the structure, we may also install fire-stop blocks and pillows that contain intumescent material by stacking and forming the elements to fit into large penetrations.
      
