            |  Spray
          p
            |  Spray-Applied Fire Resistive Materials, SFRM, has thermal, acoustical properties, and controls condensation. The primary use is to insulate steel and metal decking from high temperatures found during a fire. It is cost-efficient, quick, and highly effective. Spray-Applied Fire Resistive Materials are cementitious materials made from Portland cement or gypsum-based materials. The spray-applied fireproofing is mixed with water and sprayed onto the surface. At Titan, we use this technique as part of a building’s passive fireproofing strategy. Thickness can depend on the surface and the desired hour rating of the surface. Again, every structure requires an inspection to address all the necessary spots and locations that need fireproofing or fire-stopping techniques to prevent and restrict the spread of fire. 